content: I though this was a learning app but it just has you listen. No refund allowed.
Fantastic!...I'd give it 10 stars, but only allowed 5 currently. Need I say more? KD9QDP.
Awesome app for improving your CW speed. Like that you included the Farnsworth option. Thank you.
Ebook does not work and no way to select characters you wish to learn must be corrupted file
Love this app and how it has helped me learn morse code. Would like to see a repeat feature, allowing the user to rehear the last code sent
This is a great tool to learn CW. Can you please add a feature so that the user can connect an iambic paddle via an OTG USB dongle? Let me know if you need a tester. 73

A great app. Very, very helpful in learning Morse. There is one minor but v annoying bug with v2.28 though. My phone screen occasionally rotates while I'm marking myself. Although the rotate to landscape is ok the CW text deletes itself when the screen rotates back to portrait.
Excellent training
I no longer have tx capabilities so this app keeps my cw above 25 wpm.
Not a trainer I thought I would be able to practice, not just listen. Not helpful.
Brilliant!
Perfect app, up to 22wpm after 45 year break from ham radio. KM7Q kn
Very worst paid app. Do not purchase. Waste of money. Free app is better than this

I was looking for app that can follow me as I learn code. I have the CDs from Gordon West and I want to learn a character or two from the cd training and then use this app to randomize the characters I'm learning to reinforce that. When I get good at the characters I'm at, then I can go to the next cd lesson rather than playing the lesson over and just memorizing them. Makes practice fun. 73!

I have found this app to be brilliant. So glad to have purchased it. Now copying 20 wpm. Just have increased the space between words to 20, to give me a slightly longer break :) Copying actual QSO has taken a bit, but now getting 85%, callsigns were hardest, also adding numbers has added further difficulty, but overall very happy. Thanks 73.
Too much lag with sounding the letter and displaying the letter.
Excellent program for honing morse skills GM4EIW

It doesn't display the letter that it's beeping until after it's finished with that letter and started with the next, so you can't easily learn what it's doing in real time. That's not how I learn, so it's basically useless. Had potential, except that when I hear the beep and look at the letter, I'm always one off.
Love the speed control options, works great as i can speed up.
Please add more characters for other languages! Ä på and so on. Thanks. Otherwise the app does exactly what I want.
The best CW learning tool I've used!
I love this app. I've tried numerous others but this is head and shoulders above the rest. I let it run while travelling and my cw has improved considerably.
Excellent flexibility for learning. Limited number or practice words, it needs 500 or 1000 most common words. You can copy and paste your own text which is nice.
Best CW Trainer!
really like this app. Simple and effective exactly what i needed
Great app.
great my code copy speed doubled

I would give this app a 5 if not for the fact that eBook section has a size limit so it is not really an ebook. That is why I wanted it. I want to be able to actually read a book or at least a large text file. If you can't download a book, don't call it an eBook. Other than that, it's the most versatile and useful app for CW I have found.
This app is superb
You are a clever buggers grate app for those of us that are morse "challenged" I believe I'm in with a chance now ! Kind regards from a new be ham hopefull :-) !
Well presented and always useful
Does a great job of playing CW. Letters, numbers, special characters, and words. But that isn't at helpful in learning to send CW. Copy, maybe. Just don't see how this would help anyone learn CW.
excellent all the settings and option I need.

Very versatile, works really well, you can configure so many parameters. The only thing I miss is a delay before the message starts, or an intro sequence like VVV. Screen darkening doesn't work. I'm halfway through, looking forward to my 1st CW QSO. 73 de OE3SPR
An excellent morse code trainer that is very flexible. I can recommend it for all levels of mastery, from beginner to high speed expert.
So effective teaching tool.
Superb morse code trainer. Lots of manual settings.
Great app, the only one I use on portable devices.

This app plus the KMT Pro Morse code app is all you need to learn and or 
advance your Morse code receiving ability. I've been a Ham for over 50 
years and these two apps have renewed my copying ability up to a former 
receiving copying speed of 24+ WPM after being off CW for more than 20 years

This has helped me to jump from 15wpm to 25wpm within a few months. It's 
fantastic!

Fantastic and well polished product. The only issue I have is when playing my own text files it cuts them short, perhaps the developer could confirm if there is a limit on the size of text files that can be used with this trainer? Other than that, it's brilliant.
Love this app, really help me learning CW morse
I downloaded and  got the usual installed and this app is compatible message, but it is nowhere to be found on my phone.

This is the only CW app in the world that allows the user to vary the word spacing; essential when learning to copy text in your head. It's a shame other developers aren't interested in updating their programs and adding the features hams so desperately need. Easily worth a few Euros. Massive thumbs up to Wolphi from the Graz CW Schule!
Great flexibility for intermediate to advanced
Google just deleted all the great things I wrote about this app.

Well thought out app.  I cannot think of a single thing that needs changing or improvement.  This app gives one a wide range of control over character speed, spacing and tone.  The only thing the user need apply is the time and effort.  Well worth the money.
One off the best Learning Tool fir Morse Code. Excelent.
very well setup.  Nice to have another well made cw app..   Thanks.   Good work..

At 72 years of age it is taking me along time to unlearn trying to decode characters instead  of just listening to the sound. I passed the extra class 20 wpm test by pure logic applied to a multiple choice exam years ago.  Despite passing this test I have never had the confidence or the ability to use code on the air. Using the options available in this app I have slowly began to be able to correct my thoroughly ingrained bad practice.  It took sending characters at 40 wpm with large spacing to start to correct my problem. I have tried  many apps but this one is the only one kept on my phone. I still have a little way to go but very close to being able  to copy anything on the air. Thank you for the app.
The best morse learning app I found so far on playstore. Thanx dev for great jop.

A very flexible morse code trainer app  and perfect for the operator  who wants not only to learn morse code but extend his or her capability even further.  A free app making it even more appealing. Nice to see free software coming back into the hobby where quite often now software is often priced beyond the affordability of most operators. Big thank you to the author of this program and a credit to you sir. 73 from Peter M0JFK.
Very limited in the size of the ebook it can read.
One of the best apps I've seen for learning and increasing your ability to copy Morse code.  Feature rich, free of bugs and a well thought out interface.  Highly recommended. 73s KG5IF
I've been inactive on the band's this keeps my speed up
Excellent
Excellent
Absolutely FB app, has helped me so much, love it, keep up the good work 73 DE ZS6DLL
Excellent app to study for a Ham Radio license. Fun, easy to use. Thank you!
This app just plays cw from text.  It doesn't 'teach', not interactive at all.
Great app!  Keep up the great work!
A good simple interface, and useful tool which will help in my learning Morse..
Very complete, thought out, and works perfectly

This is far and away the best app for learning Morse code.  I've tried many apps both free and commercial and none have the full range of features found here.  The ability to practice your own sets of characters is really important as you progress through the Koch method.  Groups like 7,z,8 or s,h,4 need specific attention. And most other apps don't let you isolate such groups for specific practice.  The interface is clean and intuitive.  Try it you'll love it!
I have been a Radio Ham since 1950 but inactive for many years!  This App is flexible and easy to use!  I love the CW mode and at 80 years of age I hope to go for my extra rating.  Thanks - W3RET
Easy to configure, easy to use, interface is nicely done.  Great app for beginners or to improve speed. Well worth your time.
Two things would make this perfect: 1) an option to hide the text while copying. 2) An onscreen keypad to type as you copy (with a score displayed when you tap the stop button)

I taught morse for a couple of years and now I'm brushing up my cw after a break of many years. This app is stable, professional, technically without flaw, and better than any program/app/hardware tutor that I've used. Superb and recommended without reservation, lovely to listen to, de G4POI.
Of all the PC programmes, on line facilities and Apps this is the one that helped me most !
Great app, I love it!
The way I learned cw was from morse trainer. Everything you need is in this app. Great job.
Best ever CW app!
first rate app i give it 9 out of 10   learnt cw 30 years ago and have not used it for many years and found this app a great help to bring my reading back up to speed

This is my favorite tool for learning how to copy Morse Code. The ways to quiz yourself and all the different modes make it perfect for learning. Not to mention all the adjustments you can make to speed and tone. Awesome.
....app I've come across for learning CW.
This app helps you increase speed and stay proficient.

This app is very versatile in setting. Has to be the best one I have found yet (PC or mobile). Having the CW training at hand when wanted is very nice. Great work on this app. Look forward to any updates you can think up. This is worth all 300 pennies. 73's
The ability to change the letter speed and timings allows you to get used to fast letters at slower speeds.
Very good and handy app.
I found this trainer very easy to use! Works great.
Keep up the good work.
The best of the rest
eBook mode is a great feature!
Would be great if it would repeat the last word/letter/call sign group, doesn't seem to be a way, only play next group?

This app does everything a good CW trainer should do. I can listen to QSO's, call signs, or even my own text files. It runs nicely on my ZTE Valet Tracfone with Android 4.1. All these functions work offline! Well worth the small price.
Worked great until it stopped, now it won't even open. Waste of money, too bad, I really liked it.
replyContent: Can you please email me at info@wolphi.com and give me more details on when it stopped?  I really would like to help you getting Morse Trainer to run on your device. Thank you.

content: Crashed within 2 minutes of download and will not reopen. You will need pin and paper as you can not type as code is being sent.
Excellent. Great, fast support from developer. A real winner! If u like g4fon's pc program, you'll love this app. 73!
Excellent app
If only this app had a "send" feature it would be a perfect CW learning tool.  As far as learning to listen...it is fantastic.  Using the Koch method features is especially useful.

I purchased this app several years ago since it was the most flexible way to use Koch method of learning CW. I used to manually set the sequence of letters for Koch method. Now, with the new update, I don't need to keep a separate list of the letter sequence since it's part of the settings. Oh, there's also a setting for Farnsworth method. I'm glad I purchased this. Maybe a future feature would be an input area where you can enter your copied code to check for accuracy?
Excellent app. Love all the options. Simultaneous feedback is incredible. Beautiful app. Worth every penny.

This is, in my opinion, A Great App to learn morse code by! Very flexible and useful. Support is second to none.  I encountered an issue and was resolved immediately!  Wolphi is the best! Android 4.1.2.
Great app and fast tech support, well worth the money.

I've been a Ham for 30 years but have been away from cw for awhile and wanted to polish up my code speed.  This app is perfect.  It has a lot of flexibility and some great learning tools.  Highly recommended!
Well worth the money.

I enjoyed CW operation in the 60s, but allowed my license to lapse. This is a great tool to help dust off the old skills -- just for fun, and maybe to prepare to get back on the air. All the program's options are helpful.

I have used datong and later an MFJ 418 trainer. Both very good. This app takes Morse trainer further with easy selection of characters, qso's, numbers, words etc with quick selection of speed and sound readily available. Plus being able to scroll back over to see what was sent is straight forward. Nice app, will take a look at what else the author has to offer. :-)
Completely customizable, I set the number of dots between letters to 20 until I got better then started deceasing as I got better.
I re-purchased, after refunding months ago, because another app was disrupting the audio. It works well now and I always liked the features for training.
very effective app to learn morse code.. using my samsung 7.7 + earphone.. i can practically learn morse code anywhere anytime!
Great application to increase your speed. Bob - WR7Q

Having been continuously licensed since October of 1954, I have always loved CW and your program is the best I've seen.  Keep up the fine work!  Thank you!  Mni 73s ...   Dr. D.E. "Doc" Karlbom - W0BI Boulder, CO

All the features required; important ones are implemented well. What's all the fuss about Farnsworth, people? Set WPM to 50. Done. Now increase letter and word spacings as much as you need; decrease gradually. My only gripe is the sliders need to be full width of screen. A beginner's instructional would be nice too.
replyContent: Thank you for the suggestions.. I included a Instruction manual in the new version. The sliders are full width now too.

content: Tried them all b4 buying this one. Very happy with my choice!
I'm still working on getting my speed above 12wpm, and I love being able to whip out this tool on subways or any time I  have a free moment.  Great practice tool.

I am tired of generating code mp3s and then transferring them to my device. It's tiresome and as I am learning code, I am constantly changing the letters/numbers and WPM. This app is great, it'll do all that and more!
Doesn't have a "play a character then say it" mode. That is how I started learning on the iPhone and PC.

All features work as advertised, and more convenient than a laptop PC.  I'm back to working up my speed. The app can be used a Koch trainer  as well, just key the letters in this sequence as per Dr. Koch. ~ 73    Koch Method Sequence:  K M R S U A  P  T  L  O  W I <.> N J E F 0 Y <,>  V  G  5  /  Q 9  Z  H  3  8  B ? 4 2  7  C  1  D  6  X   <BT> <SK> <AR>              ~ ki4SGU

I downloaded the pay version of CW Trainer to my Droid Bionid and the sound was full of pops and clicks.  I emailed the author and over the course of the next week he modified the program to work with my device.  I now works perfectly.  Now that it's working I'm using it to get my word recognition up to contest speeds.  Again, excellent program and support.
Great app! No wasted space or features. Only took a few minutes on the free version to know I was buying the best app for my needs.
Great for learning cw
This is an excellent application. The best morse trainer on android market. First tried the light version and thought worth buying the full version.
Sounds like a good app but doesn't work on my Droid X.
Thank you for writing this awesome app! My CW skills have been dormant for about ten years, and this app is a great tool to get back up to speed.
Great app. Settings are flexible enough to set up as Farnworth, you just have to do the math!
The interface and configurability of the new version rocks! I listen to code practice 2-3 times a week for 20 minutes and I'm copying a solid 20 WPM!
Dear developer, have you ever tried adjusting one of those faders in the settings menu? It's nearly impossible.
Great cw learning program. David WD8CW
Perfect to practice. I used to know it,but forgot. Now getting back thanks to this app
By far the best morse code trainer on Android!!! The only thing 2 make it better would be a Farnsworth setting.
GREAT APP! Ham Extra Class -have spent yrs w MANY CW s/w tools - superior to everything I have seen or used.
Best android app yet that I've found for folks not wanting to learn CW but to simply practice and improve copy speed. Bravo!
Great App. Great support.
Excellent program. If you want to learn code this app is for you. Great for hams.
Excellent cw trainer, to up your speed. I am using HTC Desire. VK6XC. Ben.
Very good for hams learning cw. I use it in conjunction with a koch trainer on my netbook. Recommended. de Matt M6FNG
Does not "teach" just plays cw from text.
Fantastic, can now input your own text And makes it really easy to learn. Def rec app to anyone who wants 2 learn Morse Code. Great 4 HAMS. 73s W6IDJ
Nice app but after new update it goes back to renault setting evert time i launch this app
Great app
